quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  27,64,"Who originates creation, then brings it back again, and provides you out of heaven and earth. Is there a god with God? Say: 'Produce your proof, if you speak truly"
  27,65,"Say: 'None knows the Unseen in the heavens and earth except God. And they are not aware when they shall be raised"
  27,66,"nay, but their knowledge fails as to the Hereafter; nay, they are in doubt of it; nay, they are blind to it"
  27,67,"The unbelievers say, 'What, when we are dust, and our fathers, shall we indeed be brought forth"
  27,68,"We have been promised this, and our fathers before; this is naught but the fairy-tales of the ancients"
  27,69,"Say: 'Journey in the land, then behold how was the end of the sinners"
  27,70,"Do not sorrow for them, nor be thou straitened for what they devise"
  27,71,"They say, 'When shall this promise come to pass, if you speak the truth"
  27,72,"Say: 'It may be that riding behind you already is some part of that you seek to hasten on"
  27,73,Surely thy Lord is bountiful to men; but most of them are not thankful
  27,74,"Surely thy Lord knows what their hearts conceal, and what they publish"
  27,75,And not a thing is there hidden in heaven and earth but it is in a Manifest Book
  27,76,Surely this Koran relates to the Children of Israel most of that concerning which they are at variance